  "prompt": "What exactly is left-wing nationalism?",
  "response": "Left-wing nationalism is a political ideology that combines left-wing economic and social policies with nationalist sentiment. It typically emphasizes:\n\n1. Economic policies:\n- Strong social welfare programs\n- State intervention in the economy\n- Anti-neoliberal stance\n- Support for workers' rights\n\n2. Nationalist elements:\n- Promoting national cultural identity\n- Protecting national economic interests\n- Resistance to foreign economic domination\n- Prioritizing domestic workers and industries\n\n3. Key differences from right-wing nationalism:\n- Focuses more on economic justice\n- Generally more inclusive of ethnic and cultural diversity\n- Emphasizes collective economic rights over ethnic purity\n- Often internationalist in solidarity with workers globally\n\nExamples include:\n- Scottish National Party\n- Sinn F\u00e9in in Ireland\n- Some Latin American socialist movements\n- Certain anti-colonial independence movements\n\nCompared to right-wing nationalism, it's typically more progressive and less xenophobic, though still centered on national identity and interests.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
